                    <div class="icon-wrp mb-2">
                        <svg class="icon" style="font-size: 1.25em;">
                            <use xlink:href="#tooth"></use>
                        </svg>
                    </div>
                    <div class="mw-515">
                        <p class="mb-1"><strong class="fsz-18">Single Tooth Implant:</strong><br>
                            A single dental implant from Confidental in Sandhurst is a secure replacement for a missing tooth, giving you the peace of mind that you can eat and smile with confidence. You’ll forget the tooth isn’t your own.</p>
                        <p class="mb-1">A single titanium implant is placed into the jaw to replace the root. Once fitted, the implant will usually need 3 – 6 months to heal and bed into the jawbone, providing a stable base.</p>
                        <p class="mb-1">At this stage, a temporary crown is usually fitted, which will stay in place until your dentist completes the treatment and matches the colour of your crown to your natural teeth.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-6">
                    <div class="icon-wrp mb-2">
                        <svg class="icon" style="font-size: 1.2em;">
                            <use xlink:href="#bridges"></use>
                        </svg>
                    </div>
                    <div class="mw-515">
                        <p><strong class="fsz-18">Implant Retained Bridges and Dentures:</strong><br>
                            An option for patients who have lost a number of teeth in a row, is to have implant retained bridge or dentures fitted. An implant is placed into the jawbone at either end of the gap and a dental bridge or denture is used to bridge the gap. Thanks to the retaining implants, the teeth are more securely attached and less likely to slip or rub against your gums. The dentures can be removed for cleaning just like traditional dentures. Following a period of healing, the new dentures will be fitted. Temporary dentures are used whilst your treatment is taking place.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
